Firefighters are battling a vegetation fire along the West Coast Road near Atlantis. CAPE TOWN - Firefighters are battling a vegetation fire along the West Coast Road near Atlantis.Fire and Rescue s Theo Layne says there is no danger to property at this stage. It s just the vegetation that is burning, no immediate danger to property and the firefighting crew will remain on scene. Meanwhile, firefighters are continuing to monitor a wildfire on the mountain slopes above Hout Bay.Layne says water bombing efforts are continuing as the blaze remains inaccessible to ground crews.(Edited by Zamangwane Shange)